on MTN didn’t score a perfect 10 in Cape Town or the Western Cape overall was that Rain beat it in average latency. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-317653" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Cape-Town.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="857" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Cape-Town.jpg 800w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Cape-Town-299x400.jpg 299w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Cape-Town-768x1028.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Cape-Town-321x430.jpg 321w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Of all the places we tested in KwaZulu-Natal, Vodacom came closest to MTN in Durban. MTN had an average download speed of 70Mbps, while Vodacom had 63.8Mbps. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-311013" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Durban.jpg" alt="Durban mobile network quality test map and scores summary, 2019 Q2" width="640" height="800" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Durban.jpg 800w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Durban-320x400.jpg 320w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Durban-768x960.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Durban-344x430.jpg 344w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Pietermaritzburg saw much lower average download speeds than Durban. MTN posted downloads of 35.8Mbps, while Vodacom’s was 24.3Mbps. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-311007" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Pietermaritzburg.jpg" alt="Map and network quality scores summary for Pietermaritzburg — Q2 2019" width="640" height="800" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Pietermaritzburg.jpg 8