Its average download speed across all of South Africa was 33.4Mbps, while Vodacom’s was 24.6Mbps. Telkom had fractionally faster download speeds than Vodacom (24.9Mbps), but came third because its upload speeds were much slower. Vodacom’s upload speeds were 9.5Mbps, while Telkom’s were 5Mbps. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-317669" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/South-Africa.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="859" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/South-Africa.jpg 800w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/South-Africa-298x400.jpg 298w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/South-Africa-768x1031.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/South-Africa-320x430.jpg 320w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />